          "body": "The Corinthians had elevated eloquent teachers (Apollos, Peter) and ignored quieter workers. Paul reverses the order: submit (*hupotasso*) to Stephanas's household, to everyone who 'helps in the work and labors.' The same verb Paul uses of wives in Ephesians 5:22 and of believers toward governing authorities in Romans 13:1 he uses here of the Corinthians toward devoted servants. Labor, not platform, confers spiritual authority. Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus — three men we would otherwise never have heard of — receive an apostolic command of submission. The kingdom's honor-system inverts the world's. Howard Hendricks would say: the people who actually do the work in your church are the ones you ought to be following."
